(11436, -1, 'profilefield_add_edit_memberlist_text', 'cphelptext', 'If this is set to Yes, this field will be displayed on the Member''s List for each user. If you set this field as Private, only those with the proper usergroup permission will be able to see this field on the Member''s List.', 'vbulletin', 'Jelsoft', 0, ''),
(11437, -1, 'profilefield_add_edit_memberlist_title', 'cphelptext', 'Show on member''s list?', 'vbulletin', 'Jelsoft', 0, ''),
(11438, -1, 'profilefield_add_edit_optional_text', 'cphelptext', 'If this is set to Yes, the user will be allowed to fill in a text input field as an alternative to the options you have given for this field.', 'vbulletin', 'Jelsoft', 0, ''),
(11439, -1, 'profilefield_add_edit_optional_title', 'cphelptext', 'Allow Additional Field? (<i>Select, Radio only</i>)', 'vbulletin', 'Jelsoft', 0, ''),
(11440, -1, 'profilefield_add_edit_regex_text', 'cphelptext', 'You may require this field''s contents to match a PCRE-type regular expression. For example, you could have a field that is for the user''s ICQ number. Since ICQ numbers consist of only numerals, you could write a regular expression to check for non-numerals. \r\n<br /><br />\r\nExample: <span class="smallfont">(Do not start or end the expression with an escape character)</span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<b>^[0-9]{7,8}$</b><br />\r\n<br />\r\nIf you want to allow an empty response to be given, you need to account for it within the regex:<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<b>^[0-9]{7,8}$|^$</b><br />\r\n<br />\r\nSee <a href="http://www.php.net/manual-lookup.php?function=preg-match" target="_blank">PHP.net</a> for more information on regular expressions.', 'vbulletin', 'Jelsoft', 1161192426, '3.6.3'),
(11441, -1, 'profilefield_add_edit_regex_title', 'cphelptext', 'Regular Expression (<i>Select, Input, Radio, Textarea only</i>)', 'vbulletin', 'Jelsoft', 0, ''),
(11442, -1, 'profilefield_add_edit_form_text', 'cphelptext', 'This controls what page the profile field is displayed on. Most likely you want to leave this on "Edit Your Details" but if you wish to create your own user options that can be manipulated via template conditionals then select "Options". This field will then appear on the "Options" page of the User CP. Also, this field will not appear when viewing a user''s profile.<br /><br />\r\n\r\nAs mentioned, you can use template conditionals to add additional options for your users. For example, you can make this profile field a "one option" check box field under one of the "Options" categories.  You can then use the field as a conditional to display something in your postbit template.  If the "Name" of this profile field is field1 then you can use this code in your postbit template:<br /><br />\r\n\r\n<i>&lt;if condition="$post[''field1'']"&gt;<br />\r\n<font color="green">code to display if the user has checked the profile field</font><br />\r\n&lt;/if&gt;</i><br /><br />\r\n\r\nThe <font color="green">green</font> code in the middle will only be displayed if the user has checked the profile field in their options.', 'vbulletin', 'Jelsoft', 1201688570, '3.7.0 Beta 5'),
(11443, -1, 'profilefield_add_edit_form_title', 'cphelptext', 'Which page displays this option?', 'vbulletin', 'Jelsoft', 0, ''),
(11444, -1, 'profilefield_edit_text', 'cphelptext', 'On this screen you can edit this user profile field. A user profile field is a field that the users fill in during registration (or afterwards on their Edit Profile page) that can then be displayed in various places.', 'vbulletin', 'Jelsoft', 0, ''),
(11445, -1, 'profilefield_edit_title', 'cphelptext', 'Edit Profile Field', 'vbulletin', 'Jelsoft', 0, ''),
(11446, -1, 'profilefield_editcat_text', 'cphelptext', 'It is possible to group custom user profile fields into categories so that they can be logically grouped. The primary purpose of doing this is to allow different categories to be shown in different tabs or blocks on a user''s profile page (in addition to being shown in the ''About Me'' tab).', 'vbulletin', 'Jelsoft', 1205936925, '3.7.0 Release Candidate 1'),
(11447, -1, 'profilefield_editcat_title', 'cphelptext', 'User Profile Field Category Editor', 'vbulletin', 'Jelsoft', 1205936925, '3.7.0 Release Candidate 1'),
(11448, -1, 'profilefield_editcat_allowprivacy_text', 'cphelptext', 'This option controls whether the category will appear in the ''Customize Profile'' page, allowing users to select whether to hide or display the category''s profile block to other users.', 'vbulletin', 'Jelsoft', 1215167628, '3.8.0 Alpha 1'),
